Inflating solutions 
It is well known that the singularity of some static-defect solutions
can be removed by relaxing the requirement of staticity and allowing
the defect worldsheet to inflate.  Examples are domain
walls  and global strings  in
 dimensions.  It is, therefore, reasonable to check if the same
strategy works in higher dimensions.

The 4D metric of an inflating defect worldsheet is the de Sitter metric,
 
and the 4D curvature scalar is .  We solved the
equations numerically for different values of , and indeed, for
values of  above, but not too far above the critical, we were
able to adjust  so that the singularity is removed.  Two
super-critical, nonsingular solutions are shown in Fig. .  

We see that the extra dimensions in these solutions have a "cigar"
geometry, with  at large , and that the scalar
field quickly approaches a constant value, which, however, is somewhat
below .  The latter fact can be easily understood from the field
equation () for .  With  and
