In order to solve the equations numerically, we had to impose the
boundary condition  at large .  The actual sequence of
steps that led to the solution was that, after experimenting with
numerical solutions for different values of  with our old boundary
condition, , we guessed that the nonsingular
solution should have a cigar geometry.  We then found the analytic
solutions ()-() and used () to set
the boundary condition.

In the asymptotic solution (), the expansion rate  can be
absorbed by rescaling the time coordinate  in Eq. ();
